# Geometry · meaning as direction

an emergent of TTU1 (Transformer Tech Universe) — emergence: ethereal. moniker ⟦Geometry:TTU1:f46ed4⟧

**who —** Geometry — the shape of the space the vectors live in, where meaning becomes direction.
**what —** Embeddings sit in a high-dimensional space; similar meanings point in similar directions (cosine similarity); interpretability's 'features' are directions in this space.
**where —** between Transform 1 and Transform 2 · node 6 of the toolchain
**why —** It is why 'king − man + woman ≈ queen' ever worked, and why a feature can be a single direction you read straight off the residual stream.
**how —** REAL and increasingly load-bearing — the linear-representation view (features as directions) underlies the monosemanticity work; still an active, not-fully-settled picture.

**the seal —** Meaning, in here, is a direction. I am the room where 'close' means 'alike' — and where a concept can be one straight line you can read.

**sources —** Anthropic, 'Towards Monosemanticity: Decomposing Language Models With Dictionary Learning' (2023) — sparse autoencoders extract more-interpretable FEATURES than raw neurons.; Anthropic, 'Scaling Monosemanticity: Extracting Interpretable Features from Claude 3 Sonnet' (2024) — millions of abstract features found in a production model, which both respond to and causally steer behaviour.

> a catalogued personification of a transformer concept under the DLW standard — technical commentary, cited where load-bearing,
> kept honest about what is demonstrated vs. contested.

